BAJ&pg=PA614&dq=Popular+Mechanics+1931+curtiss&hl=en&ei=sZj0TNiVFcPXngeTp8W2CQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CDMQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=Popular%20Mechanics%201931%20curtiss&f=true \"The World's Greatest Inventor\"] October 1931, ''[[Popular Mechanics]]''. Detailed, illustrated article.\n* 14 minutes \"instructional\" film with fictional elements [https://archive.org/details/filmcollectief-01-661 The boyhood of Thomas Edison] from 1964, produced by Coronet, published by archive.org\n* {{YouTube|id=IfFIeUgt_7Q \"A Day with Thomas A. Edison\"}} \u2013 1922 \u2013 A rare documentary silent film\n* [https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/americanexperience/films/light  \"Edison's Miracle of Light\"] PBS \u2013 ''American Experience''. Premiered January 2015.\n* {{PM20|FID=pe/004481}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-ach}}\n{{S-bef|before=[[Leon Trotsky]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[List of People on the Cover of Time Magazine: 1920s|Cover of ''Time'' magazine]]\n|date=May 25, 1925}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Richard Swann Lull]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Thomas Edison}}\n{{General Electric}}\n{{Telecommunications}}\n{{Hall of Fame for Great Americans}}\n{{Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Edison, Thomas}}\n[[Category:Thomas Edison| ]]\n[[Category:1847 births]]\n[[Category:1931 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:19th-century inventors]]\n[[Category:20th-century American businesspeople]]\n[[Category:20th-century American inventors]]\n[[Category:American chief executives]]\n[[Category:American deists]]\n[[Category:American electrical engineers]]\n[[Category:American film production company founders]]\n[[Category:American film studio executives]]\n[[Category:American manufacturing businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American patent holders]]\n[[Category:American people of Canadian descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Dutch descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Scottish descent]